description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Band 6 Deputy Sister/Charge Nurse to join our dynamic nursing team within Paediatric Critical Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric Critical Care Unit consists of 17 level 2 and 3 critical care beds and a Critical Care Outreach service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver care to critically ill children within the Thames Valley network. We are a lead Neurosurgical and Major Trauma Centre and have a vast amount of specialities inclusive of Spinal and Craniofacial surgery, non-invasive ventilation and other multi-level surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The OUHFT Paediatric Critical Care works in collaboration with Southampton to provide a joint retrieval service, SORT (Southampton Oxford Retrieval Team). This service provides expert advice to our district general hospitals in stabilising critically ill children prior to being transferred to either Southampton or Oxford Critical Care units. It is staffed by doctors and nurses from both Oxford and Southampton, with Oxford providing our own retrieval team Monday-Friday 0800-18:00.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit offers access to international and national conferences and post graduate courses in accordance with our unit’s comprehensive development programme. We encourage and support our nursing team to complete projects for presentation or publication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to work well within the team and to be willing to work a mixed shift pattern including days and nights across the whole week. They will have at least 3 years post registration experience with a relevant course for Critical Care (HDU/ICU). They will be a self-motivated and enthusiastic individual with excellent clinical and communication skills, with an ability to lead and motivate others. They will also enjoy teaching and supporting junior staff as well as pre and post registration students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to social distancing measures and to protect our staff and candidates, interviews will be held via video conferencing. Details will be sent out if your application is successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRosie PriddyJob titleLead Outreach NurseEmail addressrosemary.priddy@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number01864 220632&lt;/p&gt;
